body:
Spacious apartment in a great neighborhood available perfect for a temporary sublet (starting as early as December 15th if needed). Available for 1-3 months. 
The apt is near the northeast corner of Central Park and has a 24 hr doorman and elevator. The apartment has hardwood floors throughout, an open living/dining room area, separate kitchen with stainless steel appliances and granite countertops, 1 full size bedroom & 1 full bath, large windows and will come fully furnished. Utilities will also be included (electric, gas, & wi-fi). 
There is a shared laundry room on each floor of the building. 
The building is 1 avenue from the 2/3 subway line and 3 avenues from the 6 subway making it convenient to get anywhere in Manhattan. The M1 bus stop is across the street from the building. 
The neighborhood is safe and also has nearby grocery stores, restaurants, & bars.
The building is located at the end of 5th Avenue's Museum Mile which includes such famous museum's as The Guggenheim and The Metropolitan Museum of Art, both within walking distance. 
We have lived in our apartment for several years and are on good terms with our neighbors. Sublettors are expected to be quiet and respectful. This space is not suitable for large gatherings/parties.

body:
Up for rent is our fully furnished apartment on the top floor of a 5th floor walk-up on a tree-lined side street in the Upper East Side. The unit is a large (630 sq ft), bright and sun-drenched, flex-2 bedroom apartment. It is conveniently located with easy access to restaurants, stores, parks, and public transit. The apartment is two blocks away from the 2nd Ave subway line. For medical students, residents, fellows, and attendings, it is within walking distance to Lennox Hill Hospital, Weill Cornell, New York Presbyterian, Hospital for Special Surgery (HSS). 

This apartment is great for individuals, couples or families who appreciate more space. The neighborhood is quiet, family-friendly and extremely safe. On Saturday mornings, there's a farmer's market right across the street bringing fresh produce literally right to your doorstep.

This is a flex-2 bedroom apartment with a large living room, dining alcove area, and a full kitchen. There is hardwood floor throughout. The apartment gets plenty of natural light and is well ventilated. The bedroom has a queen bed, nightstands, and dresser, for your use. The living room has a sofa that folds out to a full bed and a dresser. There is a single bed in the living area what makes this apartment great for 1-4 people. There are three closets, including two walk-in closets. There is also a coin operated washer and dryer in the basement.

NOTE: THE TV, SINGLE BED, BEDLINENS, BEDDING SHEETS, PILLOWS AND MULTIPLE KITCHENWARE DO NOT COME INCLUDED IN THE MONTHLY RENT RATE.

Cable/Internet is provided by RCN. Utilities are not included in rent. Cleaning lady comes every 3 weeks. 

About Room: The room for rent is a conversion, with a full wall to the ceiling (not the half walls) which was installed by the building. Most people who come into the apt can't even tell which is the 'fake' wall. Window in the room is half the size of the wall and allows for a lot of sun light. The room itself is very large;approximately 12x10. Current Roomie has queen bed,
night stand and drawers with plenty of room to spare. 

This is a resigning of the lease for (one year) dec-dec. I am currently not looking for any short term leases/rentals.

About me: 30 y.o. F dentist. I graduated from NYU dental and have stayed in the area since. I was born and raised in Brooklyn. I'm very chill/drama free and incredibly considerate. I'm super clean and neat; especially of the common area. I'm really social and outgoing, but definitely not one to bring the party home. During the week, Ill either come home and watch tv in my room with a glass of wine or I'll be out grabbing dinner/drinks with friends (huge foodie). I love discovering and trying new things. I'm also always going to concerts and different live acts. I enjoy watching sports; especially football (Jets Fan!). 

About you: I'm looking for someone I can easily get along and be friendly with. I've gone through some awful roommates in the past, and I would like to avoid that at all costs. 

Looking for someone who is clean, chill, and considerate. I am exhausted after a long day in the office and enjoy having a calm, relaxing environment to come home to. 

Feel free to conctact me with a little information about yourself and any questions that you may have. Serious inquires only please.

Lots of storage here, and we even snuck in a wine rack. The bath, also windowed, offers Danze fixtures, Toto toilet, a deep tub, a medicine cabinet mirrored inside & out, and much-improved lighting.

Pet-friendly, amenities include a live-in Superintendent, full-time Doorman & Porters, and newly renovated lobby. The landscaped roof-deck can be reserved for entertaining, bike storage is available for an annual fee of $25, the laundry room has been upgraded, elevators completely overhauled, and the boiler has been replaced,

body: This chic, designer corner 2-bedroom with river and city views. will arouse all of your senses. Enter through a gracious foyer  into a wide and airy living room; there is a separate dining area. The windowed kitchen has walnut and lacquered cabinetry, Corin countertops, mirrored backsplash, and top of the line Miele, Thermador and Leibherr appliances.  The apartment also comes with a Bosch washer and dryer.  There is beautiful millwork throughout the apartment and natural walnut floors. Sliding glass doors open onto the enormous terrace which runs the entire 31+ foot width of the living room and dining area, with views of the East River. There are two spacious, split bedrooms flanking the living room. The master bedroom features a private balcony and walk-in closet; the room offers incredible storage areas in cabinets and on the shelves of  beautiful built-ins. The en suite master bath boasts a huge glass stall shower and double sink, with custom-designed Crema D'Orcia bamboo-textured and honed Piombo tiles and Watermark fixtures throughout. The second bedroom has oversized windows that look out to the terrace, and frosted pocket doors that open to the living room. The bathroom is located outside the bedroom, for guest access as well. The bathroom has a Zuma soaking tub and Crema D'Orcia Piombo tiles and Watermark fixtures. TURNKEY READY AND BEAUTIFULLY FURNISHED.  Fantastic amenities include a 1/2 acre private park, state-of-the-art fitness center (with classes), 56/indoor pool and exclusive spa.  NO SMOKERS PLEASE. body:
Up for rent is our fully furnished apartment on the top floor of a 5th floor walk-up on a tree-lined side street in the Upper East Side. The unit is a large (630 sq ft), bright and sun-drenched, flex-2 bedroom apartment. It is conveniently located with easy access to restaurants, stores, parks, and public transit. The apartment is two blocks away from the 2nd Ave subway line. For medical students, residents, fellows, and attendings, it is within walking distance to Lennox Hill Hospital, Weill Cornell, New York Presbyterian, Hospital for Special Surgery (HSS). 

This apartment is great for individuals, couples or families who appreciate more space. The neighborhood is quiet, family-friendly and extremely safe. On Saturday mornings, there's a farmer's market right across the street bringing fresh produce literally right to your doorstep.

This is a flex-2 bedroom apartment with a large living room, dining alcove area, and a full kitchen. There is hardwood floor throughout. The apartment gets plenty of natural light and is well ventilated. The bedroom has a queen bed, nightstands, and dresser, for your use. The living room has a sofa that folds out to a full bed and a dresser. There is a single bed in the living area what makes this apartment great for 1-4 people. There are three closets, including two walk-in closets. There is also a coin operated washer and dryer in the basement.

body: There's nothing better than living in the heart of Manhattan, in a spacious 2 bedroom 1.5 bath condo (being offered furnished), within minutes of the city's best attractions and conveniences. This wonderful corner home has a lot more going for it as well, like northern and eastern exposures, lovely hardwood floors, generously-sized rooms, a windowed full bath and plenty of large closets. Limited time offer: 1 month FREE for a 5-month lease --- 
1 month free if you apply before Dec 4 and move in before Christmas or New Year.
LOVE WHERE YOU LIVE! Luxury Manhattan Lifestyle in a Stunning Building. Enjoy spectacular views from this largest one bedroom, bright and cheerful corner unit! Full of sunshine in winter! If you are not familiar with Roosevelt Island, you don't know what you are missing!! Check it out as it's the best kept secret in NYC- best of both worlds!! NYC experience yet peaceful and quiet! This is rare opportunity! No Agent Fee and 2 weeks free as a bonus!!
【Lease to take over】12/20/2018 (flexible) - 5/31/2019. Building approved. With option to renew. Also perfect for someone seeking temporary apartment, if they choose not to renew lease in June. Resident able to transfer lease to any other apartment building of Related Company in NYC, Boston, D.C., Chicago, San Francisco and Los Angeles (perfect for people expecting to relocate).
【Rent】Regular $3585/month. It is a significant saving compared to starting a brand new one-year lease. Now with the free month and a 5-month stay Jan to May, your equivalent rent is actually $2868 = $3585x4/5. Amazingly good deal! Water/gas/heating already included in the rent. 
【Building】Riverwalk Point (480 Main St). 3 minutes' walk to subway F station. 5 minutes' walk to tram or ferry. It is the newest rental building in Roosevelt Island opening in 2015. Property features: 24/7 concierge, 24/7 package pick-up, private fitness center, landscaped rooftop sun terrace, bike and resident storage, Children's playroom and so many more. Pet-friendly. Free services including hotel-style tidy up, house cleaning, mailing & return handling and so many more. 
【Apartment】The largest 1B1B in the building with stunning views. Approx. 750 SQFT corner unit. Open, bright and cheerful apartment. Full of sunshine in winter! Floor to ceiling windows with views of East River, Queensbridge Park and Queensborough Bridge. In-suite washer and dryer. Stainless steel appliances. A.C. in every room. Abundant storage room in four closets. Negotiable if you want to buy/keep the furniture.
【Commute】Subway F train 3/4/5 stops to 50 St Rockefeller Center, 42 St Time Square, 34 St Herald Square. Tram 1 stop to 60 St. Ferry 2/3 stops to 34 St East end/Wall St.
【Neighborhood】Safe, quiet, parks, playgrounds, schools, stores, restaurants. Experience all NYC has to offer and retreat to the upscale, pet-friendly, immaculate apartment.  Roosevelt Island has it all. It is the best hidden gem in Manhattan.

It is a small comfortable room within a large 4-bedroom apartment; and it is available after Dec 9. The current lease is until May 31, 2019. 

The building is located on the east side of FRD, near 25th street; and the apartment is on the 23rd floor with view of midtown Manhattan. 

There are currently 3 super nice guys living in the apartment (software engineers and NYU hospital, all in their late 20's and early 30's). 

About the apt:

Rent is $1,375 per month for your room. Security deposit of one month is also required by the building.

Electric/Heat/AC digital units are in each room (to set temp), and the bill is usually a part of the overall Waterside rent (which saves us money). Monthly costs do not usually range more than $40-$60 per person, per month.

For the internet, we use Verizon Fios; and that cost is $15 per person, per month.
Estimated Total Per Month: $1,450

**Please note you must be able to meet salary requirements/background/credit checks through the Waterside Plaza building**

24-hour doorman service, 24-hour security staff

Two-acre landscaped Plaza with panoramic, unobstructed views of the East River and Manhattan skyline (prime viewing for July 4th).

Please reach out to me with any questions at all or if you would like to set up a time to come meet the roommates.

Thanks!

1st month of rent FREE (for month of January)

Convenient location for working professionals in Manhattan and NYU Students.
20-25 minute commute (door-to-door) to Washington Square Park next to NYU main campus (off the 9th St Path Station stop).
Path trains are 24 hours and run about every 10 minutes during the day. There's a schedule online on the Path website.

There are 2 train lines (going to the WTC Path Station and 33rd St Path Station). The 33rd St Path line stops at Christopher St, 9th St, 14th St, 23rd St, and 33rd St in Manhattan. The WTC Path line stops at Exchange Place and WTC. Trains also go to Hoboken and other parts of Jersey City (including Grove St and Journal Square). The apartment is also a 13-15 minute walk to Hoboken.

1-bedroom, 1 full bathroom, kitchen
Kitchen includes dishwasher and refrigerator
684 square feet

Very safe neighborhood with security

body: This furnished apartment is a sunny and generously proportioned one bedroom apartment located on the Upper West Side. It offers a rare opportunity to take advantage of a luxurious and classic West End Avenue location.The ceiling adds to the charming and grand combination of beauty and sophistication in this wonderful apartment. The oversized living room is furnished with a relaxing sofa that has a memory foam convertible bed. There is also a dining table and entertainment area. The bedroom suite iwell proportioned and wonderfully renovated, complete with a queen sized bed. The windowed kitchen features plenty of counter and storage space and includes a dishwasher and microwave. The Bathroom, with all of it's classic fixtures, adds to the charm of this beautiful apartment. The street view side of 1871House's 2nd floor makes up the front bedroom of the Library Suite, a spacious suite whose North-facing oversized windows give a terrific midlevel portrait of the townhouse's neighbors. An original marble fireplace mantle, parquet floors, and a nearly 10' ceiling form the backdrop for this wonderfully decorated, approximately 345 square foot suite. A comfortable Ralph Lauren leather settee sits at the foot of a carved-wood queen bed with rolling-pin headboard, both of which give way to a small marble bistro table and bamboo bistro chairs. Two more marble-topped items - a Victorian washstand and Victorian dresser - complete the bedroom's primary furnishings. The prints of 18th and 19th century ante-rooms and throne-rooms along the North wall remind one of the kind of luxury that the bedroom itself hearkens back to and perhaps makes it apparent why Country Living Magazine chose to photograph the Front Library for their "Inn of the Month" feature back in the day when the 1871 House operated as a NYC-Style B&B. Please note that the Fireplace is ornamental only.

Please note that there is no kitchen or access to a kitchen in the Front Library Suite unless booked in combination with the Rear Library. Provided in the room is a small fridge & electric kettle.  The Vintage bathroom is a narrow space composed of a tiled tub/shower, pedestal sink and toilet.

The apartment occupies the complete 3rd floor the brownstone, extending from front to back and thereby providing two special sets of views: the facing row of timeless townhouses and activity of 62nd street to the north, and a cityscape view of skyscrapers, as well as the House's lovely garden below, to the south. The back portion of the apartment, facing south, consists of one twin and one queen bedroom, while the front, facing north, constitutes the main living area, including another queen bed, as well as a breakfast nook off the kitchen. The latter, offering that picturesque northern view accompanying morning coffee or dining, has a convincing claim on most delightful eating spot in the building, and it's no shoo­-in contest!

The apartment's airy expansiveness is further enhanced by the approximately 10 foot ceilings and parquet­-style hardwood floors, both of which extend throughout the suite. Two marble fireplaces, sure to draw the eye in and give perspective to the spacious suite, are found: one in the larger back bedroom and one near the front, dividing the sitting area from the queen bed there.

A kitchen, w/refrigerator, gas range/oven, dishwasher, coffeemaker, toaster oven, & supply of utensils, dishes, pots, drinking glasses & cups.

The house is located in the much sought after LENOX HILL neighborhood of the Historic Upper East side section of Manhattan and a 5 minute walk (0.2 mi) to CENTRAL PARK and some of New York's finest shopping districts. The House's location, a quiet residential enclave for some of New York's most prestigious addresses, enjoys the best of both worlds - serene privacy and un-matched convenience. The neighborhood abounds with tasteful, exclusive boutiques and charming, international restaurants. Yet, the house is only three blocks from bustling Midtown and some of the City's fabulous and world renown Museums & galleries including the Frick, The Metropolitan and MoMa.

The beautiful brownstone building is conveniently located within walking distance to the Met, Carnegie Hall, the Frick Museum, the Museum of Modern Art, Central Park Zoo & Rockefeller Center. Lincoln Center for the Performing Arts is a quick 12-minute Uber ride just across the Park or to TIMES SQUARE by Taxi or subway. We are in a perfect location for NYC Marathon Runners - as we are very close to the finish line!

The East River Esplanade is approximately a 25 minute walk.

Shopping is plentiful including Bloomingdales, Barney's, Bendel's and Bergdorf-Goodman. We are one avenue away from Madison Avenue's most select and high end boutiques. Urban conveniences make living here a breeze, and there are basic living facilities and shops within walking distance, including Whole Foods Market, Duane Reade Pharmacy, a shoe repair, dry cleaners, nail salons, hair salons, Starbucks and much more.

Public transportation around NYC is made easy from this location. Consider using the subway station at 60th Street / Lexington Avenue, which serves the 4, 5, 6, N, Q, R trains and F train on 63rd Street (all servicing up and downtown) (express and local). Bus located around the corner. The subway will take you to the Southern tip of the city (Freedom Towers - 9/11 Memorial) within 20 minutes.

The house is a six minute walk to Central Park and Fifth Avenue, 12 minutes to Times Square by Taxi and 11-14 minutes by subway; Grand Central Station is one subway stop away (take the 4 or 5 one stop from 59th street to Grand Central Station); walking distance to Fifth Avenue and Midtown East with its ubiquitous Corporate Offices as well as midtown Manhattan's exclusive Decoration & Design building (D&D building) and Manhattan Art and Antiques Center. Architects, Designers and Collectors from around the world travel to this area for its concentration of design and home furnishings showrooms and galleries.

The country's best hospitals and medical facilities including Memorial Sloan Kettering, Weill Cornell Medical College, Manhattan Eye, Ear and Throat Hospital, New York-Presbyterian hospital, Lenox Hill Hospital, the Hospital for Special Surgery and Mount Sinai Hospital are ideally located minutes away from the house.

body: There's nothing better than living in the heart of Manhattan, in a spacious 2 bedroom 1.5 bath condo (being offered furnished), within minutes of the city's best attractions and conveniences. Central Park, Rockefeller Center, Radio City Music Hall, Carnegie Hall, Times Square, the Broadway Theater District and Columbus Circle are all just minutes away. This wonderful corner home has a lot more going for it as well, like northern and eastern exposures, lovely hardwood floors, generously-sized rooms, a windowed full bath and plenty of large closets. The windowed galley kitchen with granite counters and stainless steel appliances, that includes a dishwasher, offers plenty of storage and prep space for all your culinary creations. Topping it off are utilities (electric, gas, heat and water) that are included in common charges and the comfort of having a large, full-time, onsite staff (doorman, concierge, building manager, live-in super, handyman and porter) to tend to your every need. Tower 53 also offers residents a common roof deck, laundry room and parking garage. The B, D, E, C, N, Q, R, 1 and F are all right nearby, as are fine restaurants like Le Bernardin, Yakitori Totto, Victor's Caf and Trattoria Dell'Arte, chic shopping along Fifth Avenue, the Museum of Modern Art and lots of great markets. 19h

Gramercy Park: Small studio for rent in Gramercy Park's famous Sage House, a luxury 24 hour door man building, designated a historic landmark at 4 Lexington Avenue @ 22nd Street.

For rent by owner, very bright and sunny, high floor in the Sage House, directly next door to the Gramercy Park Hotel, home of the Rose Bar and the Jade Bar.

Very very (very VERY) upscale address and neighborhood. A previous tenant of this apartment was able to snap a photo of his dog standing next to Lady Gaga as she stepped from her limo and into the GP Hotel. (The Gramercy Park Hotel, directly next door and sharing a load-bearing wall), is an Ian Schrager development, one of the finest up scale hotels in the world.

BTW, Lady Gaga's group, the Brian Newman band, appears next door every Tuesday and Thursday at the Rose Bar in the Gramercy Park Hotel. LG is reported to occasionally show up and jam.

You simply cannot live in a more upscale address than The Sage House, anywhere in the world.

$2450 per month. NEGOTIABLE. Available December 15, 2018.

First month + security = $4900 to move in.

NEGOTIABLE RENT

Reply to owner by return email. This ad will be deleted when the apt is no longer available.



Live in a bit of history:

The Sage House was built in 1916 as headquarters for a philanthopic organization, the Russel Sage Foundation, by his widow. Russel Sage was a financier who was heavily involved with the construction of the NYC subway system. The building was then purchased in 1949 by Catholic Charities and converted as a residence for retired priests and nuns. It was sold again in the 1970s and made into an apt rental building, and was finally converted to coops in 1988 by Michael Beloff. A famous below ground brothel, complete with long mahogany bar, red velvet walls, and secluded hot tubs with overhead chains (all of which survived until about 10 years ago) operated in the building's basement in the 1930s and 40s (accessed thru the side door to the building on 22nd Street). That area is now occupied by storage cages available to Sage House residents. The Sage house was declared a historic landmark in 2000.

See the building history on Wikipedia under "Russel Sage Foundation."

body:
INTRODUCTION 

I've been lived in this great apartment for 9 years and found it perfect for both living alone and now living with my wife. We're looking for someone to sublet it. It's the quintessential 1st floor East Village apartment with gorgeous 12ft ceilings and hardwood floors. It's centrally located on E.13th between 1st and 2nd literally steps from great restaurants, Union Square (4,5,6,L,N,R) and the closest L stop to Brooklyn (14th and 1st). One of the great features is you are located on the 1st floor, just up the entryway steps, but the bedroom is located in the back giving you the privacy and quiet you need. Please note the apartment can be rented FULLY FURNISHED.

LIVING ROOM

Located in the front of the apartment, the 6ft windows look out onto the street. The living room is furnished with TV, Entertainment Stand, Love Seat (that folds out into a bed), armchair, coffee table, lamps, bookshelf, high table for eating, surround sound, and two mirrors. It's a very comfy room. Once again, the apartment can come fully furnished.

KITCHEN

We've done a lot to make the kitchen comfortable and easy to cook in. There's quite a bit of usable counter space, good sized fridge, oven, and microwave. You will also get the use of pots and pans along with silverware, plates and glasses. The air conditioner for both the Living Room and the Kitchen is located in the kitchen and provides great cool air for both the Kitchen and the Living Room.. 

BATHROOM

Bathroom is pretty standard and in good, clean working order: Sink, Toilet and Shower. Good storage in medicine cabinet, under the sink and a storage cabinet over the toilet.

BEDROOM

Located in the back of the apt, the bedroom comes with a queen sized bed and a TV. It's small, but what's great is...THERE'S ANOTHER ROOM BEHIND THE BEDROOOM that's been converted into a WALK-IN CLOSET. It's a dream. People are literally shocked when they see it. While most people in NYC are struggling for storage space...this will not be your fate if you sublet this apartment.

Please email with questions or to set-up a time to take a look.

ADDITIONAL NOTES:.
- You will have someone you can call if something goes wrong in the apartment.
- First month and security due upon signing.
- Pets OK

body:
Our home is a sunny, large (1,200 SQF) one bedroom apartment with hardwood floors at the top floor of a historic, pre-war, Brownstone building. Four windows, north + south facing, exposed brick walls, a fully equipped kitchen, and French doors to a separate bedroom with windows overlooking Harlem. Shower and bath. High speed internet. A beautiful, cozy, escape away from the bustle of NYC, while only 20 min from downtown Manhattan! There is a Queen bed and comfy sofa (with fold-out Queen bed), two good ceiling fans, and often an excellent cross breeze from north-south opposing windows. This building is a Brownstone so it's not as modern as some apartments, but its beautiful, everything works, and the apartment is spotless.

Logistics: We will be away from November 2018 - June 2019 when our lease ends. If you like the place, you can take over the lease, and renew for another year/two years. Its a great flat, and we are very sad to leave, but we are moving abroad. We are subletting the apartment furnished, and the subletter is responsible for paying internet and electricity (ConEd) bills while subletting.

Security: two doors at entrance to the apartment block lead into a corridor with bike storage, with third door (to the apartment) on the fourth floor. 

Other things to note:
1. Two blocks from Marcus Garvey Park, thirteen blocks from Central Park
2. Two blocks from 2&3 trains at 125th street subway station (5 min walk max); also A/C/B/D trains at 125th St (10 min walk).
3. 15 minute walk to Columbia University
4. Great supermarkets from 5 (whole foods) to 12 (e.g. Best Yet Mkt) minutes' walk away 
5. Two handy little corner stores a stone's throw away, one with a cash dispenser. 
6. Laundromat available on opposite block and another two blocks away

Six figure renovation completed with cherry wood floors, granite kitchen, custom cabinetry. - IMMACULATE. Pristinely furnished. Barely lived in, bright and wide full one bedroom with city-views in a true white glove condominium. Pictures are of the actual unit and have not been edited. Expensive and extremely clean furniture that has barely been sat in by anyone. Generously sized windows and high ceilings make this apartment feel like a home. The open kitchen has stainless steel appliances, custom windowed cabinetry permitting light through and a black granite counter top that is extended into a full breakfast bar. Plank Cherry wood flooring runs throughout the apartment. Lighting is accentuated by hand made Italian designer Leucos' blown satin white glass diffusers (LED). The bedroom is large enough to fit an entire king-sized bedroom set and the marble bathroom has been freshly grouted. There is plenty of storage with custom built in closets. Other features include a through the wall AC / heat unit boasting 17,400 btu. All information provided is approximate.

The Cosmopolitan, built in 1986, is a beautiful meticulously maintained, full-service luxury Condominium offering: 24-hour concierge service and doormen, a private conference room on the 2nd floor, central laundry room, attentive live-in Superintendent, roof deck and on-site garage. Hello,

I have a one bedroom in our 3 bedroom triplex opening up december 1st.
The rent is $1,250.00 and the security deposit is $1,250. Utilities
are about $80 dollars more or less per person. The building is
newly-renovated and the apartment is a spacious triplex 3BR with a
rooftop and terrace. It's a half block from the subway in the
Gowanus/South slope area and is a tremendous value compared to other
places in the area. Check out the layout in the photos, as well as the
really cute dog, Kikko that you can have as a roommate.

This a a SUPER safe and friendly neighborhood. We are about 15-20
minutes from Manhattan and accessible to many different restaurants
and supermarkets.

My name is Jon. I am 29 years old and i work in the real estate
industry/construction management business. when i am not working, i
usually spend time with my gf, go to the gym and play flag
football/basketball/ rec sports. my other roommate is also a career
oriented individual who keeps it to himself most of the time. we are
not into partying on the week days and are not home that often. if
you're into football sundays and weekend game nights, we could be the
roomies you're looking for!

If interested, please email me your name & age/ current living
situation and pricing/work & salary/ and a bit about yourself. room is
available after dec 1st. Thank you & I look forward to hearing from
you!

body:
Fully furnished 2-bedroom apartment with tons of storage available for rent for the month of January 2019.  
Fully furnished, and supplied with sheets, towels and kitchen supplies. 

The main bedroom is spacious and super-sunny (3 tall windows), with a full-sized bed, a large antique desk, a Mid-century dresser, an antique armoire and a closet. The living room has a couch and a beautiful custom maple-slab dining table, a long row of closets with a skylight overhead. The small bedroom could be used as an office or second bedroom - it has a daybed that could sleep one or could be unfolded to sleep 2, as shown in photos. 

There is a European-style washer/dryer-in-one-combo inside of the bathroom. Hardwood floors throughout. High ceilings. 

This 750 sq ft (70 sq meters) apartment is located on the 3rd floor of a townhouse in a historic part of Bed-Stuy. This part of the neighborhood is quiet, residential and tree-lined, with some cute cafes and restaurants within walking distance (one cozy French restaurant called L'Antogniste is right on on the corner). The closest train, the A or C at Utica ave, is a 6-block walk, and will get you to lower Manhattan in 25 minutes (walk to train included). 
30 mins to Pratt, 35 mins to NYU.

All utilities and wifi included. Rented by owner. No fee. Security deposit required. 
Sorry, no pets. 

To help you understand the photos:
olive green room - living room
orange area - area by apartment entrance, connected to living room
light green room - small bedroom
room with funky wallpaper - main bedroom

body:
Residence Hall @ Brooklyn College is located two blocks from the Brooklyn College campus on the corner of Kenilworth Place and Farragut Road. The Residence Hall offers student housing with apartment-style living in various settings, including studios, private bedrooms, or shared bedrooms in a shared apartment with fellow students. All students are welcome from any accredited college or school throughout New York City. Three different apartment configurations are offered for 10 or 12 months terms. Prices include all utilities, basic cable, & wireless internet. Each apartment is fully furnished and includes a bathroom and a kitchenette. Layouts may vary slightly due to location of the room. Residence Hall offers students a wide range of amenities to make life comfortable and enjoyable. You can go to our site to get more information and apply as well, visit us at http://www.1kenilworth.com/index.php

*On-site fitness room

Hi,
I'm looking for someone to take on my lease finishing in June. 
The apartment is at the perfect location in Prospect heights.

It's a 5 min walk to a bunchhhh of main subway lines near Grand Army Plaza (2/3, 4/5, B, Q), prospect park and close to many groceries and a gym.

The room is huge and have a great window with a view on a tree and natural light. 
You would have your own bathroom (luxury!!).

On top of this, we have a washing machine and drying machine in the apartment as well as a dishwasher and AC for the summer. 

The apartment would be most likely furnished.

You would live with two amazing roommates. They are both friendly with 9-5 jobs. We usually hang in the living room in the evening but you could also hang in your own room (since it's so big!).

The room could be available starting Dec 10th.

You would be taking over my lease starting now and ending in June.

I want to find the best fit possible for the new roommate so make sure you write me and tell me more about and provide social media handle or LinkedIn profile. :)

The leasing company is very straight with the income. They would need to do all the credit check and make sure you are currently employed with pay stub proof.

body:
Apartment

Spacious and sunny southern-facing studio / "open 1-BR" available now in a sought-after doorman building in leafy Ditmas Park.

Clean and tidy, this sweet, peaceful, and mostly furnished apartment is perfect for an individual or couple. Furniture needs can be discussed.

At 550 sq ft, the place is well laid-out, with bedroom, living room, and dining areas, as well as a separate kitchen and dressing room, which could be used as an office space.

Hardwood floors, good heating, built-in AC.  Two generously-sized closets as well as a large linen cupboard.

The apartment has been freshly painted and updated throughout.  The kitchen features a dishwasher and newly-installed farmhouse sink, backsplash, Grohe faucet, and butcher block countertop.

Rent includes heat and hot water. Electricity and cooking gas bills reasonable.

Building has:

- live-in super
- part-time doorman 
- communal garden
- friendly neighbors
- modern laundry room
- bike room
- garage (monthly fee)

Neighborhood

The apartment is in the diverse and idyllic Ditmas Park Historic District. 

Just a 3-minute walk to Newkirk Plaza and all its amenities, including food markets, banks, post office, pharmacies, dry cleaners, restaurants, and the B/Q line.  

20-25 min to lower Manhattan, 30-35 min to midtown on the B/Q.

The popular Cortelyou Rd, which boasts tons of restaurants, cafes, bars, and a farmers' market on Sundays, is a 10-min walk or one subway stop away, and Prospect Park is likewise easily-accessible by train, bike, or foot.

Fine Print

One year lease, potentially renewable. First, last, and one month security deposit. Great credit and references required. No smoking or pets, sorry. 
Co-op application: references, credit check / financials, mgmt co review and board approval, and application fee (includes refundable move-in deposit).  

Contact for more details and to arrange a viewing!
name: Sunny, spacious studio / "open 1-BR" in Ditmas Park

body:
Hello,

We have a great room in a 3BR / 2 BA available for rent. $1600/month (utilities/internet included). If you are only here for part of December the rent can be prorated. 

It's close to the Grand st. stop on the L, across the street from a great grocery store, around the corner from a gym, bars, lots of restaurants, etc.

There is a furnished room with a Brooklyn view that has a dresser, desk, chair and queen size memory foam bed with frame. 

The common area and bathroom are cleaned once a week by a maid service. 

Utilities and high speed internet included in the rent. 

Living room has a balcony with a nice view and there's access to the large decked roof where there is an amazing view and tables/chairs. 

Laundry in the building as well as a fitness room and an underground garage if you need to store a bike.

This is a great find.

Thanks! 

_Greg

body:
We are subletting our furnished duplex apartment from end of January through June, and possibly through the summer.

It's a classic brownstone row house in Crown Heights that was beautifully renovated a year ago and offers amazing light, new high-end appliances, tons of space, and a warm and welcoming design. The downstairs has an open layout with a living room spilling into a dining area and a fantastic cook's kitchen that has too many cool features to name here. If you love to cook, you'll love the kitchen. There is also a separate front parlor room and full bathroom downstairs with walk-in shower. 

Upstairs you'll find three large bedrooms, 2 more full baths, and a big laundry room with full-size washer and dryer (this also doubles as a guest room). There are windows in every room because the house is semi-detached. Even the bathrooms receive good natural light through large interior windows and skylight. The huge master bedroom has 4 south-facing windows and is sun-drenched all day. 

Crown Heights offers plenty of restaurants and food shopping, and we're 2 express stops from Downtown Brooklyn. Super convenient to subway. Just a 2 minute walk to two subway lines (3, 4), one of which runs express to Manhattan in 15 minutes. 

We have a car and garage which may be available. For more photos, please be in touch.  

Available Jan. 27 through end of June, possibly through summer as well. This is an incredible opportunity to live in a beautiful home affordably. 

Two options for sublet:
SHARE: To rent all 3 bedrooms and shared common areas, $3950/month.
PRIVATE: For the whole space to yourselves, $4900/month.

body:
Open to two options:
Renting either just my room 
OR, Renting the whole apartment...


Sooooo here are the deets-

Move in: December 17th  (option to move in later if needed)
Rent: $3,000/month for the master bedroom/ensuite bathroom or 5,200 for the whole Apartment 
Room: King Size Bed, Electric Blinds, TV (Netflix, HBO, Amazon, Hulu, regular TV). Marble bathroom with shower, bathtub and two sinks. Walk In Closet!
Roommate: He is only going to be there for about a week or 2 during that time. There is a separate bathroom that he uses. The apartment will basically be all yours. He's never there. 
Common Area: Open Layout. Fully stocked kitchen, marble table, huge L shaped couch for entertaining and lounging around, floor-ceiling windows with beautiful views of Manhattan, fireplace.
Rooftop: 360 degree views of NYC & Brooklyn, BBQ available
Location/Transportation: The apartment is located in South Williamsburg on South 9th & Kent Avenue. About a 10 minute walk to the J,M, & Z and 15 minute walk to the L. There are also shuttles to take the train in the morning if you don't want to walk. Citibike is also an option and pretty close by. Another alternative is the Ferry, which literally stops at this building - it could take you North to North Williamsburg, Greenpoint, Long Island City and then 34th St or even South to Dumbo (also a short easy bike ride), financial district and in the summer Rockaway Beach! 
Neighborhood: There is a nice supermarket w/ draft beers and all the good stuff 2 blocks away. In addition there are tons of great restaurants/bars right on Broadway and further North in Williamsburg- think Diner, Marlow & Sons, Donnas, Baby's All Right. Also, the Farm on Kent a couple of blocks away is great for lounging. Ton's of workout options to- east river pilates, Skyting Yoga, CKO boxing you name it...
Other Amenities: Washer & Dryer. Doorman. Gym w/ a view. Computer/work room and common area.

name: 1 Bedroom - LIVE IN A BRAND NEW BUILDING!

body:
TF Cornerstone has Unit 2808, a modern, beautiful 1-bedroom apartment, available for rent at 4545 Center Boulevard in Long Island City. This 28th-floor unit has hardwood floors and stainless steel appliances. It is available for immediate move in.

The amenities for this building include:
Laundry 
24-hour concierge and gym
Lounge
Terrace
bbq grills, tennis courts and volley court

Each unit can accept one dog up to 50 pounds (non-aggressive breeds) or 2 cats. There is no pet fee.

There is a complimentary shuttle service on Center Boulevard to the 7 train station that runs every 15 minutes. Within a few blocks are the Court Square subway station for the 7, G, E, and M lines, and the East River Ferry stop, located at Hunters Point South. You are minutes away from Manhattan!

Long Island City is located on the westernmost point of Queens and is a five-minute subway ride to Grand Central Station. Among the converted warehouses and luxury condos, you will enjoy spectacular views of the Manhattan skyline and you just might know your neighbor's name. It is the perfect blend of old and new where the big city meets small town to create a truly unique neighborhood. The beautiful Gantry State Park and restaurants and nightlife on Vernon Boulevard are steps away.

TF Cornerstone has been in the real estate business for more than 40 years. We own and manage an extensive portfolio of luxury residential buildings, modern office properties and highly visible retail locations, totaling over eight million square feet throughout New York City and Washington DC, including over 7,000 luxury apartments. 

If you would like to view our available units, please visit the Leasing Office at 4545 Center Boulevard from 8am to 8pm, Monday through Friday, or 10am to 6pm Saturday and Sunday. You can also contact us at  show contact info
. No appointments are necessary.

No emails please.

2BR / 1Ba 980ft2 available jan 15, 2019

furnished 
apartment 
laundry in bldg 
I am relocating for work and would like to sublet my large 2bd apartment. The building has elevator, laundry & bicycle storage. The renovation is in process with roof deck expected to be installed in or after Spring 2019. 

The building is on 34th Ave and 82nd St (Jackson Heights), central to historic district and shopping areas. Year-round weekly farmer market is 3 blocks away (largest farmer market in Queens). Several groceries are 1-2 blocks away. There are a lot bustling restaurants and cafes on both nearby Northern Blvd and 37 Ave. Chase, Bank of America, Citi and Capital One branches are also nearby. 

Bus stop is right outside the building, with easy access to 74th Roosevelt Ave-Jackson Heights station (E,F,M,R,7) via bus 32, 33 & 49. The 7 subway stop (82nd st) is 6mins walk away.

The apartment will be furnished (seen on pic). You can use all furniture except for the TV and possibly the master bed. Apt has dish-washer.

Applicants will pay for credit check fee ($150/person) and there is no broker fee.

- Recreational and entertainment amenities offering residents the ultimate lifestyle including:

* Built-in fridge

SPA-INSPIRED BATHROOMS
* Contemporary cabinetry by Scavolini
* Porcelain tile flooring
* Decorative wall lighting fixture
* Elegant wall-mounted mirror with integrated lighting
* Grohe bathroom fixtures
* Kohler bathtub and toilet

LOCATION
* Nestled in the heart of Flushing, one of the fastest growing neighborhoods in Queens, THE GRAND is conveniently located 5 minutes from the MTA 7 train, Long Island Rail Road and four major highways. Penn Station is just 17-minutes away on the LIRR and Grand Central Station is only a 22-minute ride on the 7 train. Plus, JFK International and LaGuardia airports are less than 20 minutes away.

THE SHOPS AT SKYVIEW CENTER (http://shopskyviewcenter.com/)

body:
Victorian elegance at its finest with this turn of the century charmer. Steps to free ferry into Manhattan and next door to Historic Snug Harbor Cultural Center with Botanical gardens, Chinese Scholar's Garden, Tuscan Garden, Visual and Performing Arts Center and Children's Museum makes this mansion one of the most sought after places to be in NYC. Soon-to-be home of the largest Ferris wheel in the world, the neighborhood is definitely a place to check out. Formerly a well-known artist's castle, the home boasts 12' ceilings, 10' windows (all new), 6 fireplaces, 8 bedrooms, with formal living room and dining room, library, and eat -in cooks kitchen. Full third floor artist (writer, architects) dream studio/work space with incredible light @ 931 square feet. Have tea or hot chocolate on the Wrap around porch, only one block from the water with infamous Blue restaurant, convenient stores, cozy cafes, church, fruit/vegetable market within 1 blocks from the apartment. Another beautiful park (Clove Lakes Park) with a restaurant on the lake, paddleboats, bicycle path, track, baseball diamond, ice-skating rink, etc. and Silver Lake Golf Course are within close proximity. The St. George Theatre and Farmer's Market are all a short distance, as well.  3rd floor views of the NYC harbour. 

Great place for a group looking to stay 30 days or more. Hosts 16-24 people comfortably.
name: Furnished Rental for large groups
